The paper focuses on the behaviour of end-users while debugging Excel spreadsheets, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the design and application of a data acquisition tool, which could be considered a software engineering (cs.SE) topic. The use of Excel spreadsheets also suggests a programming languages (cs.PL) aspect. The evaluation experiment mentioned in the abstract could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY), and the development of a debugging tool could be considered a computer engineering (cs.CE) topic.
